Node.Notes: Syntactic relations of elements of this verse uncertain. Tree assumes "Mount Zion, the summits of Zaphon, the city of the great King, is beautiful in elevation, the joy of the whole earth."

Uncertain: "the sides of the north/in the far north/the summits of Zaphon." First two problematic as Mount Zion in the south and not in the north of the country. Many believe the summits of the north refer to Mount Zaphon in Phoenicia (so psalmist subverted Canaanite myth to say that Mount Zion is the real divine mount).
Tree assumes this God [is] our God forever and ever. Alternatively, could be this one [is] God, [he is] our God forever and ever.
